#: /home/pierre/dev/rust-book-fr/FRENCH/src/ch09-02-recoverable-errors-with-result.md:224
msgid ""
"Note that, like the `Option` enum, the `Result` enum and its variants have "
"been\n"
"brought into scope by the prelude, so we don’t need to specify `Result::`\n"
"before the `Ok` and `Err` variants in the `match` arms."
