#: /home/pierre/dev/rust-book-fr/FRENCH/src/ch19-03-advanced-traits.md:758
msgid ""
"To disambiguate and tell Rust that we want to use the implementation of\n"
"`Animal` for `Dog` as opposed to the implementation of `Animal` for some "
"other\n"
"type, we need to use fully qualified syntax. Listing 19-21 demonstrates how "
"to\n"
"use fully qualified syntax."
msgstr ""
"Pour expliquer à Rust que nous souhaitons utiliser l'implémentation de "
"`Animal`\n"
"pour `Chien` et non pas l'implémentation de `Animal` pour d'autres types, "
"nous\n"
"devons utiliser la syntaxe totalement définie. L'encart 19-21 montre "
"comment\n"
"utiliser la syntaxe totalement définie."

#: /home/pierre/dev/rust-book-fr/FRENCH/src/ch19-03-advanced-traits.md:776
msgid ""
"```rust\n"
"{{#rustdoc_include ../listings-sources/ch19-advanced-features/listing-19-21/"
