#: /home/pierre/dev/rust-book-fr/FRENCH/src/ch20-02-multithreaded.md:505
msgid ""
"We chose `usize` as the type of the `size` parameter, because we know that "
"a\n"
"negative number of threads doesn’t make any sense. We also know we’ll use "
"this\n"
"4 as the number of elements in a collection of threads, which is what the\n"
"`usize` type is for, as discussed in the [“Integer Types”][integer-"
"types]<!--\n"
"ignore -- > section of Chapter 3."
